to the editor in who 's poor do n't ask the census bureau op ed sept 26 jared bernstein sends a helpful message about the woeful inadequacy of the united states definition of poverty the adjustments he proposes would come much closer than we do now to measure the true and shocking poverty rate but even an adjusted measure based on better budget studies would fall short poverty is best measured in relation to the incomes of other americans economic growth should translate into rising incomes across the income scale a poverty definition that captured whether this was occurring such as a percent of median income would be a good beginning sumner m rosen judith davidoff new york sept 29 2003

